Tailwind now just applies two properties to the same class for instance when u add `delay-300` it adds the two css classes below
```
.delay-300 {
    transition-delay: 300ms;
}
.delay-300 {
    animation-delay: 300ms;
}
```
and same for `duration-300`
```
.duration-300 {
    transition-duration: 300ms;
}
.duration-300 {
    animation-duration: 300ms;
}
```
This fixes the problem for animation. But this is missing from the docs. Hopefully this gets added to the docs

_Originally posted by @arunavo4 in https://github.com/tailwindlabs/tailwindcss/discussions/3378#discussioncomment-8836346_

This PR validates incoming bare values to ensure we generate CSS that makes sense.

Before this PR, we would generate values such as:

```css
.z-index {
  z-index: index;
}

.flex-foo {
  flex: foo;
}
```

Which is invalid, after this PR, these vaues would not be generated at all.

